electrical stimuli. B: Interspike interval across the same range of electrical stimuli as in A. C: Representative recordings for a pair of cells across electrical stimuli. D: 
Comparison of rheobase before and after bath application of 1 µM semaglutide. E: Two-way plots demonstrating the effect of 1 µM semaglutide on action potential 
frequency of 5-HT neurons from group-housed mice (left) and adolescent-isolation mice (right). Remaining 3-way ANOVA comparison is shown above. F-H: 
Normalized plots showing relative changes in action potential frequency (F), interspike interval (G), and latency to first spike (H) at suprathreshold current before 
and after semaglutide application. *p < 0.05, **p < 0.01, ****p < 0.0001. 
